<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>Why might fiscal policy have a shorter time lag than monetary policy?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Fiscal policy takes longer to implement</option>
            <option letter="b">Direct government spending affects AD more immediately than interest rate changes</option>
            <option letter="c">Fiscal policy requires more political consensus</option>
            <option letter="d">Monetary policy works faster through financial markets</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>When implemented, fiscal policy through direct government spending has a more immediate effect on aggregate demand compared to monetary policy, which must work through the interest rate channel and affect private spending decisions, a process that takes more time to impact the real economy.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
